[5] Macedonia
Date: Mon 12 Apr 2011
Source: Canada MSN News, The Associated Press (AP),
thecanadianpress.com report [edited]
http://news.ca.msn.com/world/cp-article.aspx?cp-documentid=28345933


Macedonia authorities declare measles epidemic
----------------------------------------------
Health authorities in Macedonia have declared an epidemic of measles
in the Balkan country and launched an emergency vaccination program.
Health minister Bujar Osmani said on Tuesday [5 Apr 2011] that the
outbreak of the contagious disease is affecting 2/3 of the country's
territory, where half of Macedonia's 2.1 million people live.

Osmani says there have been 678 reported cases, and the expanded
vaccination program is particularly targeting the most vulnerable,
including infants and the elderly. Osmani says 30 people are
hospitalized in serious condition.

