[12] USA (Utah)
Date: Sun 10 Apr 2011
Source: ABC 4 News [edited]
http://www.abc4.com/content/news/slc/story/Four-schools-impacted-by-measles-outbreak/4T1PsoKUUk-Mzd0mKZP2pA.cspx


4 schools impacted by measles outbreak
--------------------------------------
Granite School District officials say the measles outbreak is now
affecting 4 schools in the district. Last week district officials said
only 2 schools were impacted, but over the weekend 2 more were added
to the list. Schools affected include Olympus High School, William
Penn Elementary, Evergreen Junior High, and Skyline High School.

The students who have not been vaccinated at these schools are being
asked to stay home in isolation for their own safety. The district
also announced that the exclusion date for all students and staff who
have not been immunized has been pushed back to Mon 25 Apr 2011,
because a more recent exposure period of 6 Apr 2011 has been
identified with one of the infected individuals.

The health department has advised the district that they can continue
operating schools as normal with the exclusion of the non-immunized
individuals. "We did sent a district wide call to all of our 90
schools alerting them to the situation, and telling them if they had
unimmunized students to contact their personal physicians to see how
they can alleviate the risk," said Granite District spokesperson Ben
Horsley. School related updates will also be available on the Granite
School District facebook page and twitter account.

